example.p:
Warfarin is an anticoagulant that prevents blood clotting;
often it is prescribed to stroke victims in order to help ensure blood flow.
The level of warfarin has to reach a certain concentration in the blood in order to be effective.

subsection.p:
for the long-term level of Warfarin in the patient's system. This sum has the form
a+ar+ar^2+ \cdots + ar^{n-1}
where a=5 \times 0.08 and r=0.08. Such a sum is called a finite geometric series finite geometric series with ratio r.

li.p:
The nth partial sum S_n of an infinite geometric series is

  S_n = a+ar+ar^2+ \cdots + ar^{n-1}
.
